Return the single best parse. Note that the returned tree may be missing intermediate nodes in a unary chain because it parses with a unary-closed grammar.

extractBestStateSetTree

public Tree<StateSet> extractBestStateSetTree(short gState,
                                              short gp,
                                              short start,
                                              short end,
                                              List<String> sentence)
Return the single best parse. Note that the returned tree may be missing intermediate nodes in a unary chain because it parses with a unary-closed grammar. A StateSet tree is returned, but the subState array is used in a different way: it has only one entry, whose value is the substate! - dirty hack...
